definition.value: A populated place. Un village du sud de la Tunisie (gouvernorat de Gabes).
The largest scale biogeographic division of the earth's surface based on the historic and evolutionary distribution patterns of plants and animals.
A local government region of Trinidad.
A populated place. A town on the East-West Corridor of Trinidad and Tobago.
A local government region of Trinidad.
A district of Suriname, in the northeast. Wanica's capital city is Lelydorp.
A district of Suriname. Its capital city is Brokopondo; other towns include Brownsweg and Kwakoegron.
A district of Suriname, located on the right bank of the Suriname River. Commewijne's capital city is Nieuw Amsterdam. Alliance is another major town.

A district of Suriname, situated on the coast. Coronie's capital city is Totness, with other towns including Corneliskondre, Friendship, Jenny. The district border the Atlantic Ocean to the north, the Surinamese district of Saramacca to the east, the Surinamese district of Sipaliwini to the south and the Surinamese district of Nickerie to the west.

A district of Suriname, located on the north-east coast. Marowijne's capital city is Albina, with other towns including Moengo and Wanhatti. The district borders the Atlantic Ocean to the north, French Guiana to the east, the Surinamese district of Sipaliwini to the south and the Surinamese districts of Commewijne and Para to the west.

A district of Suriname, on the north-west coast. Nickerie's capital city is Nieuw-Nickerie, the second largest city in the country. Other towns include Washoda and Wageningen. The district borders the Atlantic Ocean to the north, the Surinamese district of Coronie to the east, the Surinamese district of Sipaliwini to the south and Guyana to the west.
A district of Suriname, in the north. Para's capital city is Onverwacht, with other towns including Paranam, Sabana and Zanderij.
A district of Suriname, in the north. Saramacca's capital city is Groningen, with other towns and cities including Batavia and Boskamp.

The largest district of Suriname, located in the south. Sipaliwini does not have a regional capital as it is directly administered by the national government in Paramaribo. The main villages in the district are Apetina, Apoera, Bakhuys, Bitagron, Pokigron, Kajana, Kamp 52, Pelelu Tepu, Cottica, Anapaike, Benzdorp, Kwamalasamutu, Nieuw Jacobkondre, Aurora, Botopasi, Goddo, Djumu and Pontoetoe.
A department in Paraguay. The capital is the city of Coronel Oviedo.
A populated place. A city in Paraguay. It is the capital of the Caaguazu Department, about 150 km east of Asuncion.
A department in Paraguay. The capital is the city of Villarrica.

One of the ten departments of Haiti. It used to be part of Sud Department. The department was split in 2003, with the creation of a new department of Nippes from Miragoone and l'Anse-a-Veau arrondissements.
One of the ten departments of Haiti.
One of the ten departments of Haiti. It used to be part of Nord Department. It borders the Dominican Republic to the east.
One of the ten departments of Haiti.
One of the ten departments of Haiti, located in the center of the country, along the border with the Dominican Republic.
The newest department of Haiti, having been split from Grand'Anse Department in 2003. The capital of the department is Miragoane.

One of the 18 departments (departamentos) into which the Central American nation of Honduras is divided. It is the southernmost department of Honduras, bordering the Gulf of Fonseca to the west and the Republic of Nicaragua to the east and south. The departmental capital is city of Choluteca.
A populated place. A city in the Holguin Province of Cuba.

Un poblado rural ubicado en la comuna chilena de Paine, en la provincia del Maipo, Region Metropolitana de Santiago.
A populated place. A town.
Una ciudad, capital de la provincia de Limari.
A large village situated south-west of Stittsville, west of Richmond and north of North Gower.
A current that flows north-easterly along the Atlantic coast of Norway.
A current that originates in the Arctic Ocean and brings cold, low salinity, southbound water along the East Coast of Greenland.
